From: Oleksandr Natalenko <oleksandr@natalenko.name>
Subject: [pf-curated-6.12] amd-pstate: AMD-pstate enhancements + x86 topology hooks

Re-cut from natalenko's pf-kernel branch amd-pstate-6.12 (tip 01f72a790c8e)
as a single bulk diff, restricted to the files this overlay's curation
kept on the 6.12 LTS slot. Source: codeberg.org/pf-kernel/linux.

AMD-pstate-related changes plus the x86 topology bookkeeping
(arch/x86/include/asm/topology.h + cpu/debugfs.c + cpu/topology_common.c)
that amd-pstate depends on. Topology files also appear in amd-rapl-6.12's
touch set with identical hunks; assigned to amd-pstate.
---
diff --git a/Documentation/admin-guide/pm/amd-pstate.rst b/Documentation/admin-guide/pm/amd-pstate.rst
index 210a808b74..412423c54f 100644
--- a/Documentation/admin-guide/pm/amd-pstate.rst
+++ b/Documentation/admin-guide/pm/amd-pstate.rst
@@ -251,9 +251,7 @@ performance supported in `AMD CPPC Performance Capability <perf_cap_>`_).
 In some ASICs, the highest CPPC performance is not the one in the ``_CPC``
 table, so we need to expose it to sysfs. If boost is not active, but
 still supported, this maximum frequency will be larger than the one in
-``cpuinfo``. On systems that support preferred core, the driver will have
-different values for some cores than others and this will reflect the values
-advertised by the platform at bootup.
+``cpuinfo``.
 This attribute is read-only.
 
 ``amd_pstate_lowest_nonlinear_freq``
